This node will take some time to make it work, especially if you choose target size higher.
Wait patiently.
The first image is the mask preview, second image is mask with the area you want to put it in.
This is the image you should save

Notes from my experiments (100+) on this workflow :

1- The first image which you should put the environment image. The region you are masking should match like the object you want to put in. The region you are masking determines everything, so be careful about that. Sometimes the region is not enough, sometimes it is too much. So you should experiment how your object can fit that environment. (Masking area is everything)

2-The first image masking, which determines the context window goes to the visual text encoder should get reference from near objects size. I mean when you are masking it, there should be reference objects near so that model knows how your object size should be.

3-The second image also goes to the text encoder, mask only the object you want to put it in.

4-Our model is so sensitive to the prompt, do not make long prompt just tell what your object is, if it is not really to be determined you can say just the "object" for example "green object" or "object on womans hand". Like that.

5-Depending on your inpainting area on first image, there will be stitching problems in details, especially on edges. This will be fixed with flux fill, like the content aware fill in the future episode.

6-You shouldn't try to change existing object, it is waste of resources. Assume that there is an object on your image, you masked that object, you are trying to replace (delete the existing object and put your object) it, it is not really possible with 8 steps, model is not working like flux fill dev.


7-So pattern will be like an area that is empty, and put your object there.

8- We are working high resolutions here, and we have one most important rule here: The input resolution also determines everything, including your objects resolution! I took images from pexels.com, and most of the images are over 8MP.I mean the resolution of the environment you will put in is important. Model understands the resolution on pixels and make your image related to that resolution. This is important because we want it to be commercial ready, or at least close to that point.

9- Your prompting should be like : 

Put the object on womans hand on image 2 to the ground on image 1.
Put the bag on image 2 to the ground on image 1
Put the bottle on image 2 to the ground on image 1
Put the clothing on image 2 to the man on image 1.

10-Read carefully, you'll understand what i really mean when you are trying to work this.

Lora here,normally it is wrong to use regular qwen image lora. We should use qwen image edit lora or qwen image edit 2509 lightning lora. But i find it better to use this particular lora for my setup. You can try different and see which one fits your needs.

All of tests made with Qwen lightning 8 steps v1.1

Lora links:

https://huggingface.co/lightx2v/Qwen-Image-Lightning/tree/main/Qwen-Image-Edit-2509
